$ R package: RColorBrewer

`RColorBrewer` can be used to create colorful graphs with pre-made palettes that consist of 8 to 12 colors. In order to create more colores in a palette,
→ development/languages/R/functions/colorRampPalette[`colorRampPalette`] can be used.

There are three types of palettes:
  • qualitative: different hues emphasize different classes.
  • diverging: extrem (low and high) values are colored with dark, average values with ligher colors.
  • sequential: progress from light colors for low values to dark colors for high values.

{ Show all palettes

  gh|about-r|/packages/RColorBrewer/display.brewer.all.R||

  gh|about-r|/packages/RColorBrewer/img/display.brewer.all.png||

}
